    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nsigwinch is not taken into account.\r\nwhen using with a detach progam, the window does not get refreshed when re-attaching.\r\nThis happens with 0.9.0 (but not with 0.8.3)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nWhen I run neovim within a detach program like [abduco])(https://github.com/martanne/abduco/), via\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ abduco -e '^g' -A test nvim -u NONE\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I type CTRL+g to detach\r\n\r\nAnd reattach by re-running the previous command:\r\n```bash\r\nabduco -e '^g' -A test nvim -u NONE\r\n```\r\n\r\non several ocassions (so not all the time, but still most of the time on my machine), the screen does not get redrawn\r\n\r\nAlso sending SIGWINCH has no effect:, so I suspect 0.9.0 introduced a regression in the way SIGWINCH is handled:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nkill -SIGWINCH $(pgrep -f 'nvim -u NONE')\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have to press CTRL+L so that vim refreshes.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen reattaching / receiving SIGWINCH, terminal should redraw.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.0\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno (9.0.1420)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux arch 6.2.12-arch1-1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.12.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\narch linux package manager (pacman)",
