            "body": "Not a bug as SIGWINCH behaves as expected (resize when _window_ size _changed_). We could still do this for client that expect it as a workaround, tho for the usecase of abduco the appropriate signals would really be SIGSTOP (stop doing redraws into nowhere upon detachment) and SIGCONT  (refresh screen after attachment and then continue redrawing).",
